How to Divide by Zero

Whenever a user of some particular bit of technology migrates from product A to B, they always say "everything is faster!" Therefore, for any three products of a given technology A B and C, if a user migrates

  1. From A to B
  2. From B to C and
  3. From C back to A

Product A will now be twice as fast.
Repeating this process increases the speed of this technology exponentially, and soon it will be faster than light. Being faster than light, you can divide by zero before anybody sees what you are doing.
QED.
